{
  "title": "Groove Bank",
  "children": [
    {
      "title": "Overview",
      "lines": [
        "Rhythm templates for the",
        "chord you HOLD. You own",
        "the pitches, Groove Bank",
        "owns the timing.",
        "",
        "Hold a chord and the",
        "selected groove retriggers",
        "your notes on the beat,",
        "into the sound generator",
        "in the same slot. Change",
        "the chord mid-pattern and",
        "the next hit follows."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "How to use",
      "lines": [
        "In a chain slot:",
        " - Sound generator: any",
        "   synth (pad, bass, keys).",
        " - MIDI FX: Groove Bank.",
        "",
        "Press Play, hold a chord",
        "on the pads. The groove",
        "chops it to the rhythm.",
        "",
        "Menu: Pattern, Globals.",
        "",
        "Pattern opens the grid.",
        " - jog: cycle grooves in",
        "   the current genre",
        " - knob 1: gate (short <->",
        "   long / staccato-legato)",
        " - knob 7: swing",
        " - knob 8: switch genre",
        "Click/Back exit. Plays",
        "when Move's transport runs."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Grid marks",
      "lines": [
        "The row is pure rhythm:",
        "",
        " x  hit     A  accent",
        " g  ghost (soft)",
        " -  tie / sustain the",
        "    previous hit",
        " .  rest",
        "",
        "So 'A---' is one accented",
        "note held for four steps.",
        "Gate (knob 1) sets how",
        "long the un-tied hits ring."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Recording",
      "lines": [
        "Record the Schwung way:",
        "Shift+Sample (Quantized",
        "Sampler) resamples the",
        "chain's audio to a WAV",
        "in Samples/Schwung/."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Add Your Own",
      "lines": [
        "Grooves are plain .groove",
        "text files. Drop your own",
        "in:",
        " UserData/schwung/",
        "  groovebank/patterns/",
        "",
        "See _HOWTO.txt there",
        "for the format."
      ]
    }
  ]
}
